headline: IR Q1 Earnings Call: Management Lowers 2025 Profit Outlook Amid Tariff and Volume Headwinds
summary: Industrial manufacturing company Ingersoll Rand (NYSE:IR) met Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q1 CY2025, with sales up 2.8% year on year to $1.72 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.72 per share was 2.6% below analysts’ consensus estimates.
